{
  "info": {
    "name": "NexTest API - Security Testing",
    "description": "Complete API collection for security testing. All authenticated endpoints require a valid JWT token.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Set `baseUrl` collection variable (default: `http://localhost:3001`)\n3. Run **POST /api/auth/register** or **POST /api/auth/login** to get a token\n4. The `authToken` variable is auto-set from login/register responses\n\n## Security Testing Checklist\n- [ ] Rate limiting / brute force on login & register\n- [ ] SQL/NoSQL injection on all POST bodies & query params\n- [ ] JWT tampering (alter token, change alg to \"none\")\n- [ ] IDOR: try accessing other users' data by changing IDs\n- [ ] Mass assignment / privilege escalation\n- [ ] Path traversal on file upload & knowledge file DELETE\n- [ ] SSRF on SharePoint URL ingestion\n- [ ] API key leakage in responses / error messages\n- [ ] Password reset token brute force / predictability\n- [ ] File upload: malicious files (SVG with XSS, zip bombs)\n- [ ] Stream endpoint: DoS via slow reads\n- [ ] CORS misconfiguration\n- [ ] Token expiry & refresh handling",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "nextest-sec"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3001",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "authToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{authToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth (No Auth Required)",
      "description": "These endpoints do NOT require JWT authentication. Security focus: rate limiting, injection, brute force, info disclosure.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('authToken', json.token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', json.user.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"tester@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"StrongP@ss1\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Create account. Test: duplicate email, weak passwords, SQL injection, disposable email bypass, rate limiting."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success (201)",
              "code": 201,
              "body": "{\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...\",\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": \"6655abc...\",\n    \"email\": \"tester@example.com\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"2025-01-01T00:00:00.000Z\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Error (400) - Weak Password",
              "code": 400,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Valid email and password (min 6 characters) are required.\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Error (400) - Duplicate",
              "code": 400,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"An account with this email already exists.\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Error (400) - Disposable Email",
              "code": 400,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Temporary email addresses are not allowed. Please use a permanent email.\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('authToken', json.token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', json.user.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"tester@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"StrongP@ss1\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate and get JWT. Test: brute force, timing attack (timingSafeEqual), credential stuffing, disabled account, no-rate-limiting."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success (200)",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...\",\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": \"6655abc...\",\n    \"email\": \"tester@example.com\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"2025-01-01T00:00:00.000Z\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Error (401) - Bad Credentials",
              "code": 401,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid email or password.\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/forgot-password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"tester@example.com\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "forgot-password"]
            },
            "description": "Request password reset. Test: user enumeration (same response for valid/invalid), token leak in response, email injection, rate limiting."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success (200)",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\n  \"message\": \"Password reset link: http://localhost:3001/reset-password/<token>\",\n  \"resetLink\": \"http://localhost:3001/reset-password/<token>\",\n  \"token\": \"<reset-token>\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/reset-password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_HERE\",\n  \"password\": \"NewStrongP@ss1\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "reset-password"]
            },
            "description": "Reset password with token. Test: expired token, already-used token, weak password, token brute force, token injection."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success (200)",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\n  \"message\": \"Password has been reset successfully. You can now sign in.\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Error (400) - Invalid Token",
              "code": 400,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Unable to reset password.\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth (Requires JWT)",
      "description": "These endpoints require a valid JWT token (auto-set from login/register). Security focus: JWT vulnerabilities, IDOR, privilege escalation.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/auth/me",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
